*  Eliminates an entire class of bugs. 

*  Useful for acquiring resources and releasing them properly.

*  Useful for state machines when something unexpected happens to do
   something with the state like put it back to a default state,
   recover from the error gracefully to remain fault tolerant, print
   some error messages saying the system is in a funky state, etc.

*  For the example to use the auto_ptr run 'scons -Q auto_ptr=1' 
